<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>
    This privacy policy explains how we, Road Transport Company (RTC), collect, use, and share your personal data when you use our services or visit our website. We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting it in accordance with applicable laws and regulations.

    Personal data means any information that can identify you directly or indirectly, such as your name, address, phone number, email address, vehicle registration number, location data, etc. We collect personal data from you when you register for our services, request a quote, book a transport, contact us, or provide feedback. We also collect personal data from third parties such as our partners, suppliers, customers, or public sources.

    We use your personal data for various purposes such as providing our services to you or fulfilling our contractual obligations; communicating with you and responding to your inquiries; improving our services and website; ensuring the security and safety of our operations; complying with legal and regulatory requirements; marketing our products and services to you; and protecting our rights and interests.

    We share your personal data with third parties only when necessary for the purposes mentioned above or when we have your consent. These third parties may include our affiliates, subsidiaries, agents, contractors, service providers, customers, regulators, authorities, etc. We require them to respect your privacy and protect your personal data in accordance with this policy and applicable laws.

    We retain your personal data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which we collected it or as required by law. We take appropriate measures to ensure the security and confidentiality of your personal data and prevent unauthorized access or disclosure.

    You have certain rights regarding your personal data such as accessing it; correcting it; deleting it; restricting its processing; transferring it; objecting to its processing; withdrawing your consent; or filing a complaint. You can exercise these rights by contacting us at privacy@rtc.com.

    We may update this policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal obligations. We will notify you of any material changes by posting them on our website or sending you an email.

    If you have any questions or concerns about this policy or how we handle your personal data,
    please contact us at privacy@rtc.com..
</p>
